<p class="summary">Watching wildlife and being in nature can have health benefits. Here&rsquo;s what to watch out for in February.</p>

<h2>1. Crocuses</h2>

<p>After the snowdrops have bloomed, I always look out for the crocuses. They feel like the first signs of bright colours, in comparison to the whites, greys, and shades of brown common for winter, the best signal for the start of spring. I love the dark purples you can find, as well as the yellows, whites and white ones with purple stripes. So much so, that my photo on facebook was a cluster of crocuses for a very long time.</p>

<p>They seem to be the flower of choice for people to plant in parks and on green patches next to pavements and roads, so it can be relatively easy to find them.</p>

