<h2>2. The first blossom</h2>

<p>The first trees will bloom around this time, with blackthorn coming first. When the buds first pop, it looks like a fresh white cloud has settles on the tree. It doesn&rsquo;t last long, it feels like their only here a week before the sprinkle the ground with spring snow.</p>

<p>Over the next few months different fruit trees will blossom with whites and pinks, but there&rsquo;s something really special about seeing the first tree blossom. There are a number of fruit trees where I live, and when I see the first one bloom I try to watch the others to catch the moment when they will too. Some years I get it right, some I don&rsquo;t, but it&rsquo;s a bit of fun either a way.</p>


