<h2>3. Daffodils</h2>

<p>I always expect to see daffodils as the next sign of spring after crocuses arriving in March. However a few varieties bloom at this time, creating wonderful splashes of colour. Like crocuses, little clusters of them are often planted near roads, so they can be easy to spot. Otherwise, most supermarkets stock them too for a couple of a quid, so you can watch them bloom at home.</p>

