<h2>5. Cleavers of childish fun</h2>

<p>A staple of my childhood was a plant we called sticky stuff, though most people I knew called sticky willy. It has many, many names. According to wikipedia these are the more common ones:</p>

<p><em>Sweetheart, hitchhikers,cleavers, clivers, bedstraw, goosegrass, catchweed, stickyweed, sticky bob, stickybud, stickyback, sticky molly, robin-run-the-hedge, sticky willy, sticky willow, stickyjack, stickeljack, grip grass, sticky grass, bobby buttons, whippysticks, velcro plant and sticky plants.</em></p>

<p>If you know it then I hope this is bringing back very fun, silly memories. For those who don&rsquo;t, or need a reminder, the plant is covered in tiny, little hooks which make it perfect for sticking on your friend&rsquo;s back&#8230;creating a game like tag or it, but with a plant. Oh, for the simpler times.</p>

<p>It genuinely filled me with so much glee when I came across one of these plants as a child. I would try to cheekily stick it on my friends or sisters without them knowing, like a tiny giggling ninja.</p>

<p>In February the plant grows new shoots, so keep a look out from now to start the best game.</p>

